# SDLC Workflow

Pipeline order: `/backlog` → `/spec` → `/plan` → `/implement` → `/release` → `/retro`

## Commands

| Stage | Command | Purpose |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Capture | `/backlog` | Add a new idea as a backlog item |
| Design | `/spec` | Write design spec for a backlog item |
| Plan | `/plan` | Draft implementation plan from spec |
| Build | `/implement` | TDD implementation loop (WIP=1) |
| Ship | `/release` | Merge dev→main, version bump |
| Review | `/retro` | Post-release retrospective + ADRs |

## Rules

- WIP=1: only one item in Now lane at a time
- TDD required during `/implement`: write failing test → make it pass → refactor
- Run `make test-fast` before every commit
- Never skip pipeline stages on "just do it"
- Use `/status` to see current position in pipeline
- Use `/sprint` for batch processing all items at once